emphasized, however, that since the Go del space-time is
homogeneous, there is a closed time-like curve going through every
point in space-time.

In order to find a solution to the supergravity equations of motion
describing black holes in this background, consider an ansatz

 ds^2 &=& -f(r) dt^2 - g(r)  r ^3_L dt - h(r) r^2
(^3_L)^2 && + k(r)   dr^2 + r^2 4  ( d
^2 + d ^2 + d ^2 + 2  d d
), 
A &=& 3  2  j r^2 ^3_L  .
 
Substituting this ansatz into the equations of motion gives rise
to a rather complicated set of equations. It can be easily
checked, however that the choice

f(r) & = & 1 - 2m r^2  g(r) & = & 2 j r h(r) & = & j^2  (r^2 + 2 m) k(r) & = & (1 - 2m r^2  + 16 j^2 m^2 r^2 )^-1    

solves these equations.  In the small  limit, this solution reduces
to an ordinary Schwarzschild black hole in 4+1 dimensions.  On the
other hand, in the small  limit, we recover the Go del universe.
We therefore conclude that this background corresponds to a
Schwarzschild black hole placed inside the Go del universe. This
solution is the main result of this paper; we will study its various
properties.

The ansatz () clearly preserves 5 of the 9 isometries
of the Go del universe. They are generated by time translation
, as well as the  subgroup of the
