It is interesting to consider the embedding of the solution
() of 4+1 dimensional supergravity into string
theory. The most efficient way to do this is to first embed the
solution of supergravity in 4+1 dimensions into 10+1 dimensions.
This can be done by considering an ansatz

ds^2 = g_  dx^dx^+ _i=5 ^10  (dx^i)^2, C = 2 3   A K  ,  
where

K = dx^5 dx^6 + dx^7 dx^8 + dx^9 dx^10   . 
Indices  and  run from 0 to 4.  One can verify that
substituting this ansatz into the supergravity equations of motion in
10+1 dimensions

R_ab  - 1 12  ( F_acde  F_b  ^cde  - 1 12  g_ab  F^2) 
gives rise precisely to the equations of motion for supergravity in 4+1
dimensions (). One can now dimensionally reduce along the
 coordinate to obtain the solution () embedded
into type IIA supergravity.

In the absence of the black hole, T-dualizing along  will
give rise to a pp-wave solution obtained by taking the Penrose
limit of intersecting D3-branes. In the presence of the black
hole, T-duality yields a new black string solution for the type
IIB theory

ds^2 &=& -(1 - 2 m r^2  ) dt^2 +dy^2 - 2 j r^2 ^3_L (dt-dy)  -  2 m j^2 r^2 (^3_L)^2 

&&  + (1 - 2 m r^2  + 16 j^2 m^2 r^2  )^-1  dr^2 + r^2 4  ( d ^2 + d ^2 + d ^2 + 2  d d ) + ds^2_T^4  
where  is the coordinate dual to .  There are also non-trivial
NS-NS and R-R field strengths in the background which can be found by
following the duality starting from ().

In the limit , this new solution
() reduces to a well known pp-wave geometry. In
the  limit, the solution reduces to uncharged
black string solution of type IIB supergravity. This suggests that
() should be interpreted as the solution
describing a black string in an asymptotically pp-wave background
geometry.

There is a subtlety with this interpretation, however. If one collects
the angular part of the metric () by fixing , , and , one finds

ds^2 = r^2 4  ( (_L^1)^2 + (_L^2)^2 + (1 - 8 j^2 m)  (_L^3)^2 )  . 
In other words, the term in the deformed metric along  is
of the same order in  as the undeformed metric of the round
3-sphere.  Turning on  therefore has the effect of squashing this
3-sphere until one reaches  at which point the 3-sphere is
squashed completely.  Because of this effect on the asymptotic
geometry, the solution () cannot be interpreted as
that of a black string with the same asymptotic background geometry as
the empty pp-wave.

An important question is whether or not it is possible to find a
solution which would describe a black string which does not squash or
otherwise affect the large  asymptotic geometry of the pp-wave. It
may be that a black hole, as opposed to a black string, will have
smaller effect on this asymptotic geometry.  Similar gravitational
back reaction effects due to localized and delocalized extremal
sources were observed in. Perhaps finite energy
density uniformly distributed along the light-cone coordinates of the
pp-wave generically back reacts to deform the large  asymptotics.
It would also be interesting to examine how the Laflamme-Gregory
instability of the black string solution is
affected when  is non-vanishing.

It would also be interesting to explore various generalizations of the
solution (). For example, one can easily verify that

f(r) & = & 1 - 2m r^2  g(r) & = & 2 j r + 2 m l r^3   h(r) & = & j^2  (r^2 + 2 m) - m l^2 2 r^4  k(r) & = & (1 - 2m r^2  + 16 j^2 m^2 r^2  + 8 j m l r^2  + 2 m l^2 r^4 )^-1  
also solves the equations of motion. By taking the
 limit, we recover the rotating black hole
solution of 4+1 gravity.  One could therefore
think of this solution as a rotating black hole inside the
Go del universe. It is possible, in particular, to tune the
angular momentum

l = -4 j m 
so as to make the horizon angular velocity  vanish.

It should also be possible to find a generalization to charged black
holes by following the construction outlined in
. This will
give rise to the non-extremal generalization of the black hole solution
identified in.

There are many other interesting issues to explore. One would like
to map out the full causal structure of the black hole solution
().  It would also be interesting to find a suitable
generalization of ADM mass and angular momentum to the Go del
universe and to compute their values for () and
(). Ultimately, one would like to understand
the physical meaning of the area of the preferred screen
() and the horizon () as being related to
some microscopic state counting, possibly of strings in a pp-wave
background. We hope that the explicit solution of supergravity
equations of motion describing black holes in this background will
stimulate further insight into these fascinating issues.


